	id="Illu_ArrowLength">
	<title>Illustration: Length of an Arrow</title>
	<sub.page.body>
		<block>
			<para>The length of the arrow joining <latex>P(x_1,\dots ,x_n)</latex> to <latex>Q(y_1,\dots ,y_n)</latex> is given by the formula</para>
			<para align="center">
				<img src="ims/ArrowLength_Illstrtn.gif"/>
			</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>\Abs{ \overset{\longrightarrow}{PQ} }\ :=\ \text{dist}(P,Q)\ =\ \sqrt{(y_1-x_1)^2+\cdots +(y_n-x_n)^2}.</latex>
			</math.display>
			<para>This means that the length of an arrow is defined to be the distance between its end points.</para>
		</block>
	</sub.page.body>
